    {
      "id": "1472778375331446816",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-16T02:15:27.578+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Hey, so I was making a bunch of add-on boards for the upcoming next version of [Barnacle Board](https://github.com/Architeuthis-Flux/Barnacle_Board) and figured I'd make one that maps your 70 pin mezzanine connector to a breadboard. \nBefore I finish routing (and adding labels for the COB pads), I figured I should ask y'all some stuff:\n- Do you even want this? \n- How likely is it that you want `VDD_CORE`, `VDD_IO`, and `PWR_AUX` separate?\n- What do you generally do with `PWR_AUX`?\n- Is there anything you can think of that would make this more awesome?",
      "author": {
        "id": "746392996467179661",
        "name": "arabidsquid",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Architeuthis Flux",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "cob_media/9842f46fc73513d5203a0e33acdcbfb7-4D5CC.png"
      },
      "attachments": [
        {
          "id": "1472778375922847764",
